
ASSERTION ADDITION

MOTIVATION:
Although bad practice, it is common to
refactor an existing test case to add assertion clauses to verify
new return values from an implemented method, which is
usually done to avoid creating more than one test method for
the same code unit.

MECHANICS:

- Assign another value to an existing variable in the test
case
- Add an assertion to verify the new value that the variable
holds
- (optional) Add an assertion to verify a new magic value

